rComments: Dr. Newman has a sound grasp of theory and explains complex concepts well.  He's a real scientist.  However, he didn't seem very excited about teaching, probably because he's too busy with research to engage his students.  His slides tend to be boring and, though he can be funny, overall, he's a bit on the bland side.  Nice, but distant.

Professor Newman was an outstanding instructor!!! There are 4 exams, only 3 highest are counted, and 2 easy assignments,...the exams contain literally everything from the notes, so study them in great DETAIL...easy going TA Keisha was very nice and helpful and always has a open door. I'd recommend this class to anyone!!
